Setup Kubernetes on GCP:

Setup on local system

1. Install gcloud

2. gcloud components list

3. Install required components

gcloud components install kubectl

// " alpha
// " beta

4. gcloud container clusters get-credentials ct-cluster-1

5. kubectl run hello-server --image gcr.io/google-samples/hello-app:1.0 --port 8080

6. kubectl expose deployment hello-server --type "LoadBalancer"

7. kubectl get service hello-server

Got instructions finally from here: https://cloud.google.com/kubernetes-engine/docs/quickstart
